Install Flask:
Make sure you have Flask installed in your Python environment. You can install it using pip:
  pip install Flask

Create a New Directory for Your Project:
  mkdir caesar_cipher_app
  cd caesar_cipher_app

Create the Flask Application
Create the Flask Application File:
Create a new file named app.py and paste the provided code into it.
  touch app.py


Run the Flask Application:
Start the Flask server to make sure everything is working correctly:
  python app.py

Prepare for GitHub
Initialize a Git Repository:
  git init

Create a .gitignore File:
Create a .gitignore file to exclude files and directories that shouldn't be in your repository, such as the virtual environment.
  touch .gitignore

